OL,3,CIsle of Man becomes first parliament
OL,4,Cin British Isles to pass assisted dying
OL,6,FDoctors are free to choose whether
OL,7,Fthey want to opt-in to providing the
OL,8,Fservice, following a previous request
OL,9,Ffrom the British Medical Association
OL,10,F(BMA) that this should be a choice.
OL,12,FCampaigners opposed to a change in the
OL,13,Flaw have voiced concerns that
OL,14,Flegalising assisted dying could put
OL,15,Fpressure on vulnerable people to end
OL,16,Ftheir lives for fear of being a burden
OL,17,Fon others, and argue that the
OL,18,Fdisabled, elderly, sick or depressed
OL,19,Fcould be especially at risk.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
